images.title: Wheels up in Beijing
images.caption: Wheels up in Beijing
images.desc: The Daxing International Airport in Beijing was officially opened last week, on the 25th of September. Constructed to alleviate pressure on the city's existing airport, Beijing Capital International, the bright orange starfish lookalike took more than four years to construct. And travellers, hold onto your hats, because Daxing International will connect to China's capital city via high-speed train that travels at top speeds of more than 320 kmph.
